            <div class="reading-note" data-cid="36687570">
              <div class="short">
                
                  <span class="">存在一种色彩的象征主义，但它并不包含色彩与感受（绿色指代希望）之间的相关性。颜色恰好是感受自身的对立面，是它所获得的所有有色物的潜在连接

后一句前半译反了。

原文：
There is a symbolism of colours, but it does not consist in a correspondence between a colour and an affect (green of hope...). Colour is on the contrary the affect itself, the virtual conjunction of all the objects which it picks...</span>
                <p class="pl">
                  <span class="">2015-12-02 20:49</span>
                  
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="all hidden" style="display:none" >
                <blockquote><q>存在一种色彩的象征主义，但它并不包含色彩与感受（绿色指代希望）之间的相关性。颜色恰好是感受自身的对立面，是它所获得的所有有色物的潜在连接</q></blockquote><div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>后一句前半译反了。<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>原文：<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>There is a symbolism of colours, but it does not consist in a correspondence between a colour and an affect (green of hope...). Colour is on the contrary the affect itself, the virtual conjunction of all the objects which it picks up.<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>应译为：<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>色彩的象征主义是存在的，但它并不在于色彩与感受之间的关联（如绿色指代希望之类）。恰好相反，颜色就是感受自身，是它所接载到的所有物体的潜在连接。<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>
                  <div class="col-rec-con clearfix">
                    







